Professor Salim Abdool Karim is embarking on a new chapter. Over the past year as head of the government’s Ministerial Advisory Committee on COVID-19, he helped all of us understand the virus better.  eNCA's Sally Burdett speaks to him. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Professor Salim Abdool Karim is embarking on a new journey. He has been appointed to a nine-member scientific panel of advisors at the World Health Organization. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Professor Karim announces end of term Professor Karim served as co-chair of the inter-ministerial advisory committee over the last year. He recently stepped back from the role to resume his work on HIV and AIDS research.